      <h2>1. Jackery HomePower 3000 — Best High-Capacity Power Station</h2>
      <p><strong>Rating: 4.8/5 ⭐</strong></p>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FGHLKGPW?tag=sciencesolved-20">Jackery HomePower 3000</a> is the most popular high-capacity power station on the market, and for good reason. With 3072Wh of LiFePO₄ storage and 3600W continuous output (7200W surge), it powers almost anything you can plug into it — including a full-size miter saw, a compressor, and multiple lights simultaneously.</p>
      <p>The integrated hand truck with oversized wheels is a standout feature for contractors. At roughly 70 lbs fully loaded, you wouldn't want to carry it, but rolling it across a job site is effortless. Fast AC charging recharges the battery in about 2 hours, and 1200W solar input means you can top up from panels during lunch breaks. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FGHLKGPW?tag=sciencesolved-20">Check current pricing on Amazon</a>.</p>

      <h2>2. Oscal 3600SE — Best Raw Capacity Runner-Up</h2>
      <p><strong>Rating: 5.0/5 ⭐</strong></p>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GWHKXZ7D?tag=sciencesolved-20">Oscal 3600SE</a> matches or exceeds the Jackery in nearly every spec: 3600Wh capacity (higher), 3600W output with 6000W surge, LiFePO₄ chemistry, and built-in wheels. It's a direct competitor to the Jackery HomePower 3000, often at a more competitive price point.</p>
      <p>Early reviews are outstanding — a perfect 5.0 rating from early adopters. For contractors who need maximum runtime for a full crew over multiple days, the extra 528Wh over the Jackery could mean the difference between finishing the day or running back to charge. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GWHKXZ7D?tag=sciencesolved-20">See latest pricing on Amazon</a>.</p>

      <h2>3. VTOMAN 3096Wh with Extra Battery — Best for 12-Output Versatility</h2>
      <p><strong>Rating: 4.3/5 ⭐</strong></p>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CWGJ3ZL8?tag=sciencesolved-20">VTOMAN 3096Wh Power Station</a> takes a different approach: 1500W continuous output (3000W peak) but with up to 12 output ports. That's enough AC and DC outlets to power every device your crew brings to the site simultaneously — phones, radios, headlamps, tools, and a work light all at once.</p>
      <p>The expandable battery design means you can add extra battery packs for longer runtime. The 3096Wh baseline with an extra battery included makes this a strong contender for jobs where connectivity and device charging matter as much as raw tool power. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CWGJ3ZL8?tag=sciencesolved-20">Check current price on Amazon</a>.</p>

      <h2>4. OUPES Mega 1 — Best Expandable Mid-Range Station</h2>
      <p><strong>Rating: 4.6/5 ⭐</strong></p>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DG8JQNS4?tag=sciencesolved-20">OUPES Mega 1</a> hits the sweet spot for solo contractors who need honest power without the bulk of a 3000Wh unit. At 1024Wh base capacity with 2000W continuous output (4500W surge), it runs a circular saw, lights, and laptop charging for a full day.</p>
      <p>The killer feature is expandability: you can add extra battery units to reach up to 5kWh total. That means you start with a compact, carry-anywhere unit and scale up as your needs grow. UPS mode (sub-20ms switching) protects sensitive electronics. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DG8JQNS4?tag=sciencesolved-20">See latest pricing on Amazon</a>.</p>

      <h2>5. 1800W Power Station (1382.4Wh) — Best Compact Powerhouse</h2>
      <p><strong>Rating: 5.0/5 ⭐</strong></p>
      <p>This <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GY91Q345?tag=sciencesolved-20">1800W Portable Power Station</a> with 1382.4Wh LiFePO₄ battery is perfectly sized for contractors who need more than a camping station but don't want to haul a 70-lb monster. At roughly 30 lbs, it's genuinely portable — one hand up a ladder, into a truck bed, or across a scaffolding plank.</p>
      <p>The 1.3-hour fast charging is industry-leading for this capacity class, and the 15ms UPS switching means your tools and electronics are protected during grid flicker. With a 3000W surge rating, it starts stubborn motors without tripping. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GY91Q345?tag=sciencesolved-20">Check current pricing on Amazon</a>.</p>

      <h2>6. LIVOWALNY 550W Inverter — Best Ultra-Compact Tool-Battery Option</h2>
      <p><strong>Rating: 4.0/5 ⭐</strong></p>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FLQ5Y1XM?tag=sciencesolved-20">LIVOWALNY 550W Power Inverter</a> is a different animal entirely. Instead of an internal battery, it runs off standard DeWALT 20V tool batteries. If you already own DeWALT tools, you already own the batteries — this is just the inverter body.</p>
      <p>At 550W continuous output (pure sine wave), it's enough for lights, laptop charging, radios, and small task lighting. It won't run a saw or compressor, but for a finish carpenter or electrician who just needs to keep batteries charged and phones topped up, this is the most compact, lightweight option available. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FLQ5Y1XM?tag=sciencesolved-20">See latest pricing on Amazon</a>.</p>

      <h2>7. Commercial-Grade Mobile Energy Storage — Best for EV Charging & Heavy Rescue</h2>
      <p><strong>Rating: New Release</strong></p>
      <p>This <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GYV9NT76?tag=sciencesolved-20">Commercial-Grade Mobile Energy Storage Charging Station</a> is built for a different category of contractor — think heavy equipment operators, EV charging installers, and emergency rescue teams. It's a high-power portable EV charger and backup power source rolled into one rugged mobile unit.</p>
      <p>If your job involves powering or charging electric vehicles on site — whether it's a construction EV, an electric work truck, or customer EVs in a parking lot — this is the tool for the job. It's also useful for outdoor rescue and disaster recovery operations where grid power is unavailable. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GYV9NT76?tag=sciencesolved-20">Check current pricing on Amazon</a>.</p>

      <h2>8. Honda EB10000 Generator — The Gas Baseline</h2>
      <p><strong>Rating: 3.6/5 ⭐</strong></p>
      <p>We include the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08DJ9XF32?tag=sciencesolved-20">Honda EB10000</a> as a baseline comparison. At 10,000W of continuous gas-powered output, it still dominates in raw power. But at 200+ lbs, deafening noise levels, and constant fuel and maintenance costs, it's increasingly hard to justify for most contractors. The 3.6 rating reflects the frustrations of heavy maintenance and noise complaints on job sites.</p>

      <h2>How to Choose: Decision Framework</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>You need max runtime for a full crew →</strong> <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FGHLKGPW?tag=sciencesolved-20">Jackery HomePower 3000</a> or <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GWHKXZ7D?tag=sciencesolved-20">Oscal 3600SE</a></li>
        <li><strong>You're a solo contractor who carries gear up ladders →</strong> <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GY91Q345?tag=sciencesolved-20">1800W Power Station (1382.4Wh)</a></li>
        <li><strong>You want expandable capacity on a budget →</strong> <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DG8JQNS4?tag=sciencesolved-20">OUPES Mega 1</a></li>
        <li><strong>You need maximum outlet ports for a team →</strong> <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CWGJ3ZL8?tag=sciencesolved-20">VTOMAN 3096Wh</a></li>
        <li><strong>You already own DeWALT batteries and want ultra-portable power →</strong> <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FLQ5Y1XM?tag=sciencesolved-20">LIVOWALNY 550W Inverter</a></li>
        <li><strong>You need to charge electric vehicles on site →</strong> Commercial-Grade Mobile Energy Storage</li>
      </ul>

